OK, I know it's weird to give a random fast-food place five stars, but this place does not disappoint. It's like the only non-chain fast-food place that's open late and serves more than just burgers and hot dogs (although it does serve those, too). The gyros and chicken gyros are really good and very filling, but my favorite thing right now is the veggie sub. It's packed with cheese, yummy fresh veggies and topped with just the right amount of oil and vinegar to make the bread nice and moist. This place is always busy, too, which is a good sign. It's like the owners wanted to run a fast-food joint but still put the care and attention into their menu that you'd find at a sit-down, bar and grill setting. There's no booze here, but go next door to Capone's while you're waiting and peruse their extensive beer selection!
